BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
To find the [`x`]-intercept:

[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
3x-2y\amp=12\\
3x-2(\substitute{0})\amp=12\\
3x\amp=12\\
x\amp=4
\end{aligned}
```]

So the [`x`]-intercept is at [`\left(4,0\right)\text{.}`]

To find the [`y`]-intercept:

[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
3x-2y\amp=12\\
3(\substitute{0})-2y\amp=12\\
-2y\amp=12\\
y\amp=6\ldots
\end{aligned}
```]

So the [`y`]-intercept is at about [`(0,-6)\text{.}`]

